	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=12002&amp;mid=104887788243186">RE: Proc and DMG bonus</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=12002&amp;mid=104887788243186#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Fri, Mar 28th 2:33 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=96483"><span id="Scholar">Mourn</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">18 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Good [4.24]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>The person who submitted the picture is either a bard, a rogue or a beastlord, that's why you see the damage bonus.&nbsp;&nbsp;The bonus that appears on an item is tailored to the person wielding it.  Caster types never get a damage bonus, thus when a caster equips it, none appears.  So it hasn't been nerfed in terms of bonus damage.  In addition, bonus damage can vary due to class and level, so what appears here as 11, could be 7 for someone else, or 15 for another.<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Mar 28 13:59:20 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
